l'obiettivo della linea di ricerca è quello di definire un framework che permetta di fare capacity planning per eventi reali

okay qual è l'idea che c'è nel nostro framework

3 righe di motivation
3 righr di obiettivo (costruire un framework basato su dati sotirci che permette di fare stress test e capacity planning)
3 approccio (raccolta dei dati reali, ambienti di simulazioni, riproduzione dei dati con eventi aggiuntivi)


With the ever-growing popularity and attendance of e-Sports competition, the design of the network architectures which support these events has never been of such importance. Choosing the right dimensions and capabilities of networks has been more of a guessing game throughout the years, rather than a systematic approach to determine the right size, without over or under-provisioning the necessary resources. One recent case of this phenomenon has been the notorious "Lucca Comics & Games" festival: various stand workes have complained about the capacity of the network that the event has offered them in support of their activity.
With this preliminary paper we want to introduce a framework, based on real-world historical data, that enables domain expert to stress test their designed networks and perform a more precise and detailed capacity planning.
To address this challenge, we collected and analysed real-world data from the UPSIDE event held in Naples on June 28–29, 2024. By capturing and examining all traffic on the event's network architecture, we developed a systematic framework for guiding network professionals in designing efficient and scalable infrastructures for future festivals and conventions. 
The collected data have been then packaged in a dataset can be replicated in a modular and scalable fashion over networks to test their reliability and resiliency on different scale of traffic. Furthermore we've used the same dataset to analize unwanted or malicious behavior on networks and study the different effects they may have and how they can affect them.





